  "texts": [
    "Then, participants performed the emotion aggregation task as in the previous experiment.",
    "However, on each trial, after indicating their choice, they were also presented with the response of an AI algorithm for 2 s (Fig. 1a).",
    "The participants were then asked whether they would like to change their decision (that is, from more sad to more happy and vice versa) by clicking on the yes or no buttons (Fig. 1a).",
    "Before interacting with the AI, participants were told that they \"will be presented with the response of an AI algorithm that was trained to perform the task\".",
    "Overall, participants performed 300 trials divided into six blocks."
  ],
